  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT210-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">pirintu vanta talaimakaṉ naṉku āṟṟuvittāy (G2: talaimakaṉai naṉku
          āṟṟiyiruntāy) eṉṟāṟkut (C1: eṉṟārkkut) tōḻi uraittatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Told by the confidante to him who said “you have
          reassured [her] well!”, [that is] HIM, who came after being separated. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT210">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l>tiṇṭēr naḷḷi kāṉat taṇṭar</l>
          <l>pallā payanta neyyiṟ ṟoṇṭi</l>
          <l>muḻutuṭaṉ viḷainta veṇṇel veñcō</l>
          <l>ṟorukalat tēntiṉuñ ciṟiteṉ ṟōḻi</l>
          <l>peruntō ṇekiḻtta cellaṟku</l>
          <l>viruntuvarak karainta kākkaiyatu paliyē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>Even if [it] received a pot</l>
          <l rend="indent2">of a hot dish of white rice stewed together with the whole</l>
          <l rend="indent3">of Toṇṭi's ghee, given by the many cows</l>
          <l rend="indent4">of the herdsmen in the forest of Naḷḷi with firm chariot</l>
          <l>– a trifle</l>
          <l>as offering for the crow who croaked [he] will come for the feast,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">because of the distress which emaciated the big shoulders</l>
          <l rend="indent10">of my friend.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
